#)What is a Final Argument?

A final argument means a method parameter declared with the keyword final.
When you declare a parameter as final, it means:
ğŸ‘‰ The variable cannot be changed (reassigned) inside the method.



//////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
public class Main {
    void show(final int number) {
        // number = number + 1;  âŒ  Not allowed! (compile-time error)
        System.out.println("Value: " + number);
    }

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Main obj = new Main();
        obj.show(10);
    }
}
